Princess Maria-Olympia of Greece and Denmark, simply known as Olympia, is a 25-year-old fashion model, socialite and member of the Greek Royal Family. On Thursday night, the royal attended the Eternity Charity Fundraiser hosted by Lola Bute. This charity night was in support of Action On Addiction, James' Place, Place2Be and Grow at Alva Coachworks.  The Greek royal looked sensational at the London event. She wore a Yves Saint Laurent leopard-print silk dress The dress is no longer in stock, however previously retailed for £1,415. The dress was a straight line, finishing around the Princess’ shins. READ MORE: Kate and William show 'emotional exhaustion' after 'comments by Harry' It was sleeveless, showing off her tanned, toned arms. The Princess paired this gorgeous midi dress with a pair of Aquazzura Tequila Plexi 105 sandals in orange. The showstopping stilettos are £950 to purchase from My Theresa and look sensational on Olympia. The strappy design is covered in crystal embellishments and sits on a sky-high stiletto heel.  Olympia styled her gorgeous blonde locks in a slightly wavy fashion, which finished just below her shoulders. She also wore bold red lipstick to complete her jaw-dropping look. Royal fans loved Princess Olympia’s style and took to social media to comment. Instagram user @margee48 said: “Beautiful Princess.”  Similarly, Instagram account @clemiechaz added: “In love with her shoes.” Royal fan @sofipusarelli commented: “Divine! “She looks more a model than royal. “She doesn’t have to stick to any dress code.”  Royal watcher @jantinori1 said: “She looks fabulous.” Princess Olympia is the oldest child and only daughter of Pavlos, Crown Prince of Greece and his wife, Marie-Chantal Miller. Her paternal grandparents are Constantine II of Greece and Anne-Marie of Denmark. This royal couple was the last King and Queen of the Hellenes. 